This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) as it presents a novel method for learning an interpretable classifier using an ensemble of weak learners. It also involves the use of random subsets of features, which is a common technique in machine learning. Additionally, the paper may also fall under the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data mining (cs.DM) as it involves the development of a new algorithm for classification. The paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of computational engineering (cs.CE) and cryptography and security (cs.CR) as it discusses the interpretability of the learned rules, which is important in these fields.
